version_description: It has the all of the chords, the last version only has the intro.

I have looked at all of the tabs for this song and the only one that is close is Version 3. I am not saying that the others are wrong but maybe slightly misleading to a beginner. I just think that these chords work and gel together ........

This tab is mostly based on Corey's Warner acoustic performance, published on the Youtube-channel The Rock Reel (https://youtu.be/mH19wwuL6cM). Notice that during the first verse he only plays root notes instead of complete chords.
I've determined that Corey Taylor uses a B5/G in the third measure of verses based on observations from this [video]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mH19wwuL6cM).
1st version of st marie in chords.
